 The International Hope Barometer Survey Research Program is conducting a survey on levels of hope and other positive psychological characteristics among South African adults. The research is done in collaboration with an international team of researchers from Switzerland, Spain, Portugal, France and Germany. The survey has been approved by the University of Johannesburg’s Faculty of Humanities Research Ethics Committee. To participate in this survey, click on the link below: https://www.efs-survey.com/uc/HSG/0c94/  Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 